'''Jack Steinberger''' (born [[May 25]], [[1921]]) is a [[physicist]]. He co-discovered the [[muon neutrino]]. He won a [[Nobel Prize in Physics]] in [[1988]].

Steinberger was born in the city of [[Bad Kissingen]] in [[Bavaria]], [[Germany]], but left at the age of 13, due to the increasing [[anti-Semitism]] of the rising [[Nazism|Nazi]] party.  He moved to the [[United States]], where he lived for many years, before moving to [[Switzerland]] to work at [[CERN]].

